name: One-Pot Moroccan Shrimp Tagine
author: SunnyDaysNora
summary: The rich, exotic flavors of Morocco shine through in this delicious, one-pot shrimp tagine dish!  Serve over prepared couscous.
ingredients: 1 large russet potato, peeled and diced
½ cup pitted Kalamata olives, sliced
1 (1.41 ounce) package sazon seasoning with saffron (such as Goya® Azafran)
1 pound uncooked medium shrimp, peeled and deveined
directions: Heat a Dutch oven over medium-high heat
Saute carrots, onion, potato, and bell pepper until soft, about 5 minutes
Add olives, garlic, and ginger paste and saute for 2 minutes
Stir in tomatoes, cilantro, parsley, cumin, seasoned salt, sazon, paprika, turmeric, lemon juice, cayenne, black pepper, and bay leaf
Cover and cook until tomatoes have broken down and flavors have combined, about 20 minutes
Add shrimp, cover, and cook until they are bright pink, about 5 minutes
